<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id744dcd53-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s126"><num value="126">§ 126.</num><heading> National Hispanic Heritage Month</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The President is requested to issue each year a proclamation—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id744dcd54-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s126/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> designating September 15 through October 15 as National Hispanic Heritage Month; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id744dcd55-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s126/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> calling on the people of the United States, especially the educational community, to observe National Hispanic Heritage Month with appropriate ceremonies and activities.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id744dcd56-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(<ref href="/us/pl/105/225">Pub. L. 105–225</ref>, <date date="1998-08-12">Aug. 12, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/1259">112 Stat. 1259</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
